<br>
I'm not sure where Funcom got their MA knowledge but to the best of my Knowledge Katana's (both Ninja and Samurai) were 2he weapons not 1he. Musashi of course being the caveat emptor to my generalization. The current sword forms that I study in TKD are katana based and 2HE in nature, I'm pretty sure the Japanese traditions teach the same.<br>
<br>
The point. Why are there no 2he MA req weapons for us in the game? I have used a weapon since beta, at release I went Eblade which wasn't bad but now I want something cheaper IP wise and I like my 2he concept for this character. I have every QL 200 2he I could find in the game on this character and not one of them uses MA as a req. SO once they nerf our ability to use any non-MA req weapon my concept and all that IP is wasted.<br>
<br>
Currently this character is using a Copper Burning Katana and although the damage is small albeit radiation damage it is by far the absolute coolest looking weapon I have ever seen used on a MA. I get a big smile on my face every time I F8 out and watch Takuan hack, slash and punch his way through a mob. It would make the late Toshiro Mifune proud (Japanese star of many Akira Kurasawa films).<br>
<br>
<br>
So Funcome GIVE ME MY DAMN 2HE KATANA WITH MA REQ's.<br>
<br>
